description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a (full time posts at 37.5 hours post per week) enthusiastic Pharmacy Technicians to support a new project at Furness General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a qualified (GPhC registered) Pharmacy Technician, be competent, able to prioritise work and have the ability to implement change as well as manage and develop services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to lead the team in organising and prioritising workload efficiently and effectively, working accurately in a timely manner in the face of frequent interruptions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will be committed to improving patient care and delivering a high quality pharmacy service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shifts will be on a rota basis covering 6:00 to 20:00, 7 days per week. Shift pattern will be confirmed at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participation in Weekend and Bank Holiday rotas is required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anyone newly appointed to the trust will be subject to the completion of a satisfactory 6 month probationary period (this includes bank staff). This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the role and working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAndrea ScottJob titleAssistant Chief Pharmacy TechnicianEmail addressandrea.scott2@mbht.nhs.ukTelephone number07970349998&lt;/p&gt;
